Kru: "Wow, there's only one bed here."
Umi: "Is there a problem with there being only one?"
Kru: "No, but that means one of us has to sleep somewhere else, right?"
Umi: "Hm? We can just sleep together. Umi always sleeps with Mii-A."
Kru: "Eh! No! That's... that's a problem!"
Umi: "There's no problem. The bed is fluffy and makes for a good sleep."
Kru: "Hmm... I wonder if it's really okay."

Kru: (...What should I do? My heart's pounding and I can't sleep at all.)

Kru: (Every time her back touches me, I can feel Umi's softness and
warmth.)

Kru: (Doesn't Umi feel anything...? It's so embarrassing to be the only one
feeling flustered...)
Umi: "Kru... are you still awake...?"
Kru: "Eh! Ah, yeah, I'm still up..."
Umi: "I see... Umi can't seem to fall asleep either..."
Kru: "Yeah... I can't seem to fall asleep either."

Umi: "The kingdom is amazing... It's different from the village Umi lives
in..."
Kru: "Yeah, the sheer number of people is overwhelming..."

Umi: "Yeah... But everyone seems so lively, I don't dislike it. The castle
had a bad atmosphere though."

Kru: "That's true. Most of the people in the castle are nobles, so there's
an air of looking down on the townspeople."
Umi: "Yeah... Are there other towns too?"

Kru: "Ah... I haven't been to many myself, but there are various towns.
There are different people, different foods, and different ways of life
there."

Umi: "That's amazing... Umi wants to incorporate various things into her
village too. Different foods from different towns."
Kru: "It opens up a world of possibilities."
Umi: "Yeah... a world of dreams."
Kru: "Umi...?"
Umi: "What?"
Kru: "No, it's nothing..."
Umi: "I see..."
Umi: "...Hey Kru..."
Kru: "What?"
Umi: "Somehow... I can't fall asleep because my heart is pounding."
Kru: "Eh, you too, Umi...?"
Umi: "Yeah... it's definitely different from sleeping with Mii-A."
Kru: "Well, that's... yeah."

Umi: "Yeah... We have to walk a lot tomorrow, so I'll try my best to
sleep."
Kru: "Yeah... I'll try my best too."
Umi: "Zz-Zz-"
Kru: "She fell asleep, huh... I should try my best to sleep too..."
Kru: "Good morning, Umi."
Umi: "Good morning, Kru. It's a nice morning."
Kru: "Yeah... it's a nice morning indeed."
Kru: (As expected, I was so nervous I could hardly sleep...)
Umi: "Kru, shall we depart?"
Kru: "Yeah, let's go."
